Shock can be defined as a condition of insufficient delivery of oxygen and nutrients to meet the metabolic demands of the body. Oxygen delivery (DO2) is directly proportional to cardiac output and the oxygen content in arterial blood (CaO2). Cardiac output depends on heart rate (HR) and stroke volume. Stroke volume is a function of preload, myocardial contractility, and afterload.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
